line_2: " That doth the smallest Sin commit,
The Breadth, and Length, and Depth, and Height
In one, no object of our sight,

line_1: As speaks the Hand, that form'd them, Infinite:
line_2: But shining with such vast, such various Light,
That these fair Stars, these Objects of Delight,
And Terror, to our searching dazl'd Sight,
Till it ascended to that glorious Height,
Then shall this scene, which now to human sight
Ay, quick return'd the impetuous Knight▪
As from an urn, all to delight,

line_1: Till all my sense is lost in infinite,
line_2: And one vast object fills my aching sight.
